<DocsLayout title="Smart Dispatch" section="Dispatch">
  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Field Promax offers smart scheduling tools to optimize your operations. The <strong>Calendar & Map View</strong>
    helps reduce travel time by clustering work orders on a map, while the <strong>Job Status View</strong>
    provides real-time updates on technician progress.
  </p>
  <p>
    These features reduce travel time and miles driven, saving costs. The Job Status View is your
    "eye in the sky," giving you real-time visibility into where every job stands.
  </p>

  <h2>How to Access</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>From the left panel, select <strong>Scheduling and Dispatching</strong></li>
    <li>Choose <strong>Map and Calendar</strong> or <strong>Job Status</strong> view</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Calendar & Map View</h2>
  <img src="/images/dispatch/smartscheduling_01.gif" alt="Calendar and Map View" />

  <h3>Smart Dispatch</h3>
  <p>
    Reduce travel time and optimize routes by clustering work orders on the map.
    See where technicians are in relation to pending jobs.
  </p>

  <h3>Map Features</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Work Order Locations:</strong> Open work orders displayed on the map</li>
    <li><strong>Technician Locations:</strong> Marked by truck icons showing live positions</li>
    <li><strong>GPS Updates:</strong> Technician locations update every 8-10 minutes when tracking is enabled</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Live Job Status View</h2>
  <img src="/images/dispatch/smartscheduling_02.webp" alt="Job Status View" />

  <h3>Real-Time Calendar</h3>
  <p>View work orders based on their current status with color-coded indicators:</p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Status</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Assigned</strong></td>
        <td>Work order appears grey when assigned to a technician</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Accepted</strong></td>
        <td>Changes color when the technician accepts the job</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>In Route</strong></td>
        <td>Updates when the technician is traveling to the job site</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Checked In</strong></td>
        <td>Shows when the technician has arrived and checked in</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Completed</strong></td>
        <td>Marked when the job is finished</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Notifications & Permissions</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Technicians</strong> must enable location tracking in the mobile app for their positions to appear on the map</li>
    <li>Status updates are reflected in real-time as technicians update work orders in the app</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Tips</h2>
  <div class="callout callout-tip">
    <p>
      <strong>Use the Job Status View</strong> to get real-time visibility into technician progress.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Optimize routes</strong> using the Calendar & Map View to reduce driving time.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Ensure location tracking is enabled</strong> for all technicians to get accurate positioning.
    </p>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
